title: This Is The King's Singers 1980
description:
This Is The King's Singers is a compilation album from 1980 with pop and jazz selections from albums released 

prior to 1980.

Tracks
	1. I'm A Train
	2. Girl Talk
	3. The Windmills of Your Mind
	4. I Love You Samantha
	5. Ring De Banjo
	6. God Bless Joanna
	7. The Slow Train
	8. It Was Almost Like a Song
	9. Strawberry Fields Forever
	10. The Gambler
	11. Didn't We
	12. After the Goldrush
	13. Dayton Ohio 1903
	14. With You on My Mind
	15. One of Those songs
	16. A Transport of Delight
	17. I'll See You Again
	18. Life on Mars
 <a href="
http://www.kingssingers.com/p//this-is-the-king~s-singers/op53.html" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://www.kingssingers.com/p//this-is-the-king~s-singers/op53.html</a>

The King's Singers appearing on this album are:
	Nigel Perrin & Alastair Hume - Counter Tenors
	Alastair Thompson or Bill (Greyston) Ives - Tenor
	Anthony Holt & Simon Carrington - Baritones
	Brian Kay - Bass

This album is no longer released commercially, but may be found on eBay and Amazon.

Note -- On February 1, 2014 the group announced that some of their earlier albums will be released digitally, 

however this album is not listed.   <a href=" http://www.kingssingers.com/2012/news.php?nid=401" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://www.kingssingers.com/2012/news.php?nid=401</a>
